Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
justifyBudget(25.10)                                      justifyBudget(25.10)

Name
       justifyBudget  -  Queries  and verifies the timing budgets generated by
       the Innovus software

Syntax
       justifyBudget

       [-help]

       {<partitionName> | <instanceName>}

       {-pins <pinList>}

       [-outfile <fileName>]

       [-summary]

       [-view <viewName>]

       Queries and verifies the timing budgets generated by the Innovus  soft-
       ware. You can also query budgets selectively for some/all partitions or
       instances.

       The justifyBudget command honors the report_timing_format global, which
       allows  you  to  customize the timing report according to the specified
       columns. You must set this global before  specifying  justifyBudget  or
       deriveTimingBudget -justify to get the report in the desired format.

       Note:  In  case  of  combined budgeting, the justifyBudget command will
       justify all the input or output delays attached to the port of a parti-
       tion.

       The justifyBudget command only supports the -summary parameter in  MMMC
       mode  (the  default mode). The report will contain only the headers. To
       print paths, use deriveTimingBudget -justify.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information for each justifyBudget parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man justifyBudget

       <-outfile fileName>
              Specifies the output file name that contains timing budget  data
              for a pin.

       <partitionName> | <instanceName>
              Specifies  the  name  of the partition/instance to analyze. When
              used with -mergeClones, the software reports the worst-case data
              for specified partition/instance pins in  the  master/clone  set
              containing  the  partition/instance. The <instanceName> can only
              be specified when the  deriveTimingBudget  command is used  with
              the -inst option. In default partition mode, the <partitionName>
              is specified.

       -pins <pinList>
              Specifies  the hierarchical partition pin(s) to be analyzed. You
              can use * to specify all pins.

       -summary
              Displays the style summary report containing the header  section
              of the full report to show budget calculation only. Use this pa-
              rameter after using saveTimingBudget/savePartition.

       -view <viewName>
              Prints  a report for the specified view. If you derived the tim-
              ing budget in MMMC mode (default), this parameter is required to
              obtain a report.

Examples
              * For examples of budgeting for MMMC  designs,  see  the  Timing
                Budgeting chapter of the Innovus User Guide.

              * The following command generates the timing budget data for the
                pin input of partition/instance partition1 and prints a report
                for view SETUP_VIEW1:

                justifyBudget partition1 -pins input -view SETUP_VIEW1

              * The following command generates the timing budget data for all
                pins  of the partition/instance partition1 and prints a report
                for viewing HOLD_VIEW1 in the file justifyData:

                justifyBudget partition1 -pins *  -outfile  justifydata  -view
                HOLD_VIEW1

